    "qa_beats_nonqa_shell_here": "NO",
    "qa_beats_steinmetz_here": "YES: the direct dimensioned QA shell integral outperforms the log-linear Steinmetz baseline on this selected Ring35 SIN subset.",
    "qa_lifted_vs_nonqa_shell_here": "MIXED: calibrated QA J/Pi shells have higher held-out R2 than ordinary H/B shell binning, but worse MAE/RMSE. This is not yet a clean QA-specific win.",
    "qa_not_random": "YES: QA-only held-out models reduce error substantially relative to the mean-loss baseline on real measured loops.",
    "shell_result_interpretation": "The raw physical loop integral is the expected upper-bound sanity check. Ordinary non-QA H/B shell binning explains most of the direct shell result and beats the joint (b,e) QA state shell by MAE/RMSE. A lifted QA J/Pi shell slightly beats non-QA by R2 but not by MAE/RMSE, so this run supports finite-shell hysteresis mapping and only a mixed, not decisive, QA-specific advantage."
